This paper deals with image classification using deep learning architecture, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of auto-encoders, which are a type of neural network commonly used in unsupervised learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of features for classification, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with histology images, which are a type of medical imaging, and thus could also be classified under multimedia (cs.MM).
